// E0223 extern_multi_out: a `#foreign` proc with TWO independent out-only out-params (`twovals(x)(a, b)`)
// must be REJECTED. A C extern returns exactly one value (the single out-only out-param maps to it); a
// kernel-written extra output must be an in-out buffer param (a name in BOTH lists). Before this check,
// arche SILENTLY miscompiled it: it declared `i32 @twovals(i32)`, dropped the 2nd out-param, and bound
// garbage to both — a soundness hole. (Supporting genuine multi-return externs is separate feature work;
// this is the correctness fix that turns silent corruption into a clear error.)
// RUN: %arche build -o %t %s > %t.out 2>&1 ; grep -qF "out-only out-params" %t.out
#foreign {
  twovals :: proc(x: int)(a: int, b: int);
}

entry :: system {
  twovals(5)(a:, b:);
}

#run entry
